<cl=A2A2A2>
Hunters do not admit people with too high a degree to their guild, because they don't like magic. When they have to do magical experiments, anything good rarely comes out of this, given their poor knowledge of the elements. Neither can hunters boast of strength and endurance. Years of hunting are not wasted though and hunters are the most precise marksmen in Sphere! Besides, being constantly engaged with monsters of any kind, hunters have mastered the art of protection from both military and magical attacks. These warriors know how and where to strike to cause the most damage. This art is called "squirrel's eye." Accustomed to constant travels in search of prey and capable of chasing the most swift animals, hunters can develop a truly impressive speed if they like. Only hunters manage to put two bolts at once into a usual arbalest and not to miss!

<br>
